HEADWORD: Three-torque system of control
<hw>Three"-torque` system of control</hw>. <fld>(Aeronautics)</fld>
<def>Any system of rudders by which the pilot can exert a turning moment
about each of the three rectangular axes of an aeroplane or
airship.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Three-valved</ent>⟦br⟧
